                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hello and thank you for reading my post.
<br />

<br />
My background in EQ:  i started way back in 2000 on my druid, i played on and off for a few years and i just took my last break 8 months ago, my druid was level 65 with about 200+ aa almost time flagged,  i came back about a month ago and decided i didn't want to be a 2end rate class (druid).  i have always wanted to play an enchanter because i love to crowd control and playing in GoD groups with charmed enchanter pets and the challenge of dealing with a pet that could drop the group in seconds seems like a lot of fun to me.
<br />

<br />
Now i have a level 34 enchanter, full twinked out in about 100k of gear, i have been reading these forums almost every day and always keep on top of the general forum for EQ.
<br />

<br />
It seems like the enchanter class isn't what i thought it was.  crowd control isn't what it used to be (OS, KC, Guk ect) and charming has recently been nerfed it seems.
<br />

<br />
Is the enchanter class gone down hill that bad or does everyone magnify the small problems in their class because they want to be all powerful again? im not sure if i want to continue with my enchanter if all i have to look forward to is tash/slow/crap nuke and rare crowd control and nonexistent charming.
<br />

<br />
Basically in a nutshell, all i read on this forum is negative posts about enchanters and enchanter quitting and the class dieing, is this true? should i just start another class while i can still turn back without to much time spent on my enchanter? or is it just magnified small problems and the class is still useful and fun?
<br />

<br />
Thanks for your time and opinions.
<br />

<br />
Synist</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
