                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The problem is that you can't reasonably 'determine for yourself'.  By the time you invest the amount of time it takes to build up a decent character, the investment is already too large to simply go back and start over if you decide you don't like the class.
<br />

<br />
If you plan to play at a high level, my advice would be to pick any class except for enchanter.  While it may seem hard to believe, i think druids are actually in better shape right now so i'd even say stick to that before starting an enchanter.  Thats saying a lot since druids are pretty awful right now and show no signs of getting any better.
<br />

<br />
There is nothing to cc outside of raids at high level and charm is useless at least in oow.  I can't see it being useful in the future either.  The devs are intransigent about improving enc slowing and you can't even pretend to compete without getting a serpent (which requires you to somehow go back and farm an expansion which is now quite old).  Caster dps and non-healing casters in general are pretty useless with the exception of their ability to buff melee dps (like shamans) or improve healer mana regeneration (like necros).
<br />

<br />
The raid situation was actually quite decent in the mpg raids and tacvi.  There are adequate roles for cc and even when there isn't a role for cc, there is at least some blurring of class disparities.  If you look at mpg tactics raid, a smart enchanter can outdamage e.g. a stupid wiz or rog, which is not the case in most other raids.  In what i've seen of anguish and don raids, however, there is little of importance but the standard tank/heal/dps junk so again raiding becomes pretty dull.
<br />

<br />
Soloing is pretty much dead for just about anyone.  You can solo/twobox trivial content as an enchanter better than most, but there's not a lot of value to doing so.  Reverse charming is your only means of doing so now, and if there is ever anything enchanters are able to solo, it will just get nerfed by making it summon anyway.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> im not sure if i want to continue with my enchanter if all i have to look forward to is tash/slow/crap nuke and rare crowd control and nonexistent charming. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Unless you are going to almost exclusively raid and solo trivial mobs, thats all you're going to do judging by current content.  Anyone else who tells you differently is either delusional or selling something (like yet another new expansion).</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=648415" target="_blank" class="postlink">Londo Mollari</a> (retired)
<br />
-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1192270" target="_blank" class="postlink">Pojke</a>
<br />
 Tholuxe Paells</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
