                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">im not sure if i want to continue with my enchanter if all i have to look forward to is tash/slow/crap nuke and rare crowd control and nonexistent charming. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
It is as Londo says. 
<br />

<br />
For exp grinding purposes, at high end (KT, MPG, RSS) you are lucky if you get to use mez once every 2 hours. Casters are sucky DPSers compared to melee DPS, except maybe a necro (or a shaman with the new DoN proc spell). You can charm, but the average DPS of the charmed pet is not all that much better than your animation DPS (considering redebuffing and recharming downtime, along with wipe potential), and just a tad better than a DC pet, if so (if charmed pet is not hasted, a DC pet would prolly be more DPS). Not worth wiping the group when it breaks and starts hitting you or everyone around for over 1K DMG IMO.
<br />

<br />
So expect to tash, slow, crap nuke and rare mez.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Crowd control is not really as nerfed as is said I don't think.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Crowd control is not nerfed, just non-existant in the high end. With mobs hitting for 1300ish peeps will just not allow mez and will CC on pull. Mainly because zones are designed for single pulling as a consequence of mob DPS.
<br />

<br />
At high end, 1 add can wipe group if you get unlucky on resists, but shouldn´t if you are PoTime equiped or similar and have your rune AAs done (ER and Mind over Matter). 2 adds on the other hand will already require a tank with a lot of HPs, and unless you get lucky enough to mez both adds without any resists (or at least the 1st add you cast mez on), 90% of the times tank will die, and prolly ends up in a wipe.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">You will always find yourself in a group with a puller who can't pull or a tank with less hp then you lvl 13 ranger alt with no gear. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
If what you are saying is that the only hope for chanter fun is to group with peeps that suck, your grouping experience will suck accordingly. 
<br />

<br />
The thrills of locking down a multipull and saving the day are too few and far in between.
<br />

<br />
If you don´t mind pulling, but still feel like mezzing here and there when needed, I suggest you make a bard instead.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
