                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">First I said my fully buffed Animation pet does <span style="font-weight: bold">about</span> half the damage of some of the charmed ones. I've had some Charmed MOBs hitting only in the low 200's and some even dropping down to the high 100's. Fully buffed my Animation is a much more <span style="font-style: italic">reliable </span>pet in most OoW zones. 
<br />

<br />
I duo with a cleric a lot and I can farm Harbringers, DS, BF, and NC with just my Animation. I hold aggro and Cleric keeps me healed while I nuke and pet does the spanking from behind. Only mana breaks cleric needs are when I need smoke =:~P
<br />

<br />
I may be wrong about the nerfage in GoD but I could have swore they had a nerf patch where more MOBs were made uncharmable and some, as it appeared to me, were hitting for less. It's been 6 months since I was in GoD xping so my memory could be faulty and if it is I apologize for the mistatement. 
<br />

<br />
Also note I personally consider any zone that doesn't have a DC mob for me, that doesn't have charmable MOBs, or where Charmed MOBs are hitting for less then when not charmed a nerfed zone.
<br />

<br />
Now my pre OoW Animation didn't do as much in GoD as my current one does but in OoW zones, especially WoS and MPG I won't charm I'll only use my Animation although I do keep a Charm memmed but only for emergency CC.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Foreverwise
<br />
70th Season Epic Coercer of Prexus 
<br />
Allies Undivided
<br />
Innoruuk
