                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There were 2 KT+ 'nerfs' from the chanter perspective.  When KT/Ikkinz were first released you could charm there and many of the mobs were of the appropriate level to charm.  There was a nerf that flagged all of the mobs in KT and ikkinz uncharmable.  Shortly after, there was another 'nerf' that increased the mob levels in KT in response to complaints that xp in KT was poor compared to pofire and poearth.  Prior to this, the level range was 62-66 i think and it seems like all mobs were just increased by 2 levels.  Nobody but paladins and enchanters much cared about the difference, but of course the intelligent thing to do that doesn't mess up stuns and wom/colour cloud would have been to just up the zem.  After the release of oow, all mobs in pre-oow zones level 65 and up were blanket flagged immune to charm.  This made sure there was no charm damage available in qvic or txevu outside of raid events.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">He did not say his animation was 'better' then a charmed mob, he said fully buffed it did 'about half the damage'. The point at which the animation becomes half the damage of a charmed pet is OoW.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
If you mean exactly half, i don't know if that ever occurred.  The point at which charm damage dropped to where it was no more than approximately double that of animation damage was KT.  Charm was not rendered useless only with the release of OOW.  It happened with the charm nerf to KT and since that point it has not provided substantially greater xp than the animation.  To those far behind in content, it might seem like charm was only recently removed from the enc skillset, but its been over a year.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=648415" target="_blank" class="postlink">Londo Mollari</a> (retired)
<br />
-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1192270" target="_blank" class="postlink">Pojke</a>
<br />
 Tholuxe Paells</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
